notes: The v local neurons (cell types vLN24-29) recorded in Schlegel et al. 2021 (https://doi.org/10.7554/eLife.66018) and the current paper (Supplemental file 1) are included in the ALv2 lineage. This is because, though the cell body fibres of the vLNs do not clearly co-fasciculate with ALv1 or ALv2, Lee et al. 2020 (https://doi.org/10.7554/eLife.53518) demonstrated that the ALv1 lineage only has projection neurons in the secondary neurons. In the larval connectome (Winding et al. 2023, DOI: 10.1126/science.add9330), the ALv1 and ALv2 lineages have one tract identified together as BAla1/2. This tract contains the picky LNs (Berck et al. 2016, https://doi.org/10.7554/eLife.14859), but the particular lineage identity (ALv1 vs. ALv2) cannot be ascertained. Overall, while the vLNs could be early-born neurons in ALv1 or ALv2, we feel that it is more likely for them to be in the ALv2 lineage.
